<font color="#FF0000">RESPONCE TO STEPHANIE</font><br>
<tt>Sun Feb  2 11:44:25 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
My name is Donald Frederick i served with 1st Cavalry Division.First in the infrantry with 7th cav 65 66 second<br>
in the 2/20th arieal rocket artillery jan 67 june 67.Third<br>
with c troop 1/9th Aug 70 May 71 last two as door gunner.I<br>
have read all above and like the onlookers at a hold up their views are all different because of a lot of reasons.<br>
Having said that,and with no malice towards any of the above<br>
i would like to say the following.<br>
1.On my first tour with A.Co 1/7th(GARRY OWENS)I was wounded<br>
3 bullets and asorted schrapnel.In the most terrible battel<br>
for me in the war.when my tour was up went home on free thirty day leave before going back.At that time (Dec 66)I did not here of or see any anti war activities.Gave a class at the local high school and stated we could win.<br>
2.After second tour all my thoughts were getting even with<br>
the enemy not about politics.I killed far more enemy from<br>
the air then on the ground.Went home on medivac.Got out of<br>
ft devans hospital and went to FT campbell for 1 year,got married and reinlisted.spent 20 months in germany,had a ball<br>
and put the war out of my mind.<br>
3.Got levied out of germany for third tour,and at that time<br>
had a 4 month old daughter.On a concience level DID NOT want<br>
to go back but as with first two tours had the same guilt<br>
feeling as everybody else,about leaving friends behind without the job being done.Having been out of the country and not keeping up on the news and shutting out news of the<br>
war I had not been exposed to the Anti War Movement.<br>
4.At this time we lived in Kentucky where my wife was from<br>
and it was not the hot bed of dissent even at this stage in<br>
the war.But the indifference and lets talk about something <br>
elese were there.When I returned home in May 71 thru oakland<br>
that was the time it hit me like a hammer.we were the bad guys not the nva.you remember the nva the ones who used hue<br>
to show the world,if anybody listened,how things would be<br>
done when the war was over.So being viewed as the bad guys<br>
like the rest of my companions we with drew and kept the fact that we were ever there.<br>
5.After al theese years,two failed marriages and finally<br>
getting help from the VA with lots of medication and counsel<br>
ing.I have now made it back to a point where I can say yes<br>
I was there and did my best and would have done the same<br>
giving what had led up to the vietnam war as a teenager.<br>
Kennedy,no one to get even with.Ask not,What your country<br>
can do for you and so on.We in our teens wanted to fight<br>
those commie bastards.We did not take a lot of prodding,so<br>
don't kid yourselves.We went because we wanted to.Yes we were ignorent of the history of vietnam,had we had any<br>
knowledge of the vietnameese we would have known a country<br>
who fought or was ocupied by the chineese for 12 hundred<br>
years were not going to be vanquished by uncle sams boys in<br>
a short war which is the only kind AMERICA will fight in as<br>
we hold life and materials so dear to us we would not commit<br>
to a lot of casulties,no stomach for that.<br>
6.So in closing I would like to say to all on both sides of<br>
the war it is over,except it and move on.Yes for us it is<br>
hard to swallow,but nobody cares.If you are saying no no we<br>
care we have learned our lesson,you are decieving your selves.Look at those four RANGERS who tried to hold off the<br>
human wave attacks on the down chopper in Africa.only to be<br>
dragged down the street for the world to see.Can you here<br>
them around the world?When will they ever learn??Marine barracks in Saudia Arabia.REST OF WORLD&lt; still have not learned yet.HEE HEE.I am not even going to get to bosnia.<br>
So if they ask in a historial sense did we americans learn<br>
from the most horrific war of how not to get involved the<br>
answer is NO&gt;&gt;.with the exception of the desert storm war up<br>
to the point of Bush taking over from the generals we did<br>
not learn much.You do not quit till the mission is over...I don't care if it was for Shell oil&lt;Big Corperations or for<br>
&quot;our friends in the aera&quot;.Which when we need them would not<br>
give us the time of day.<br><br>
Here's hoping you will forgive the ramblings of a not highly educated man.But one who was there and would wish the<br>
rest of the country would wake up and take responsibilty for<br>
what your elected officals do with our Military.Before the<br>
harm is done to our people and our standing with the rest of<br>
the world is Destroyed.<br>
If you would like to e-mail me at home,don1@iamerica.net.<br>
Thank you for you time in reading this.
